<head>TURTLE</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>TORTOISE</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">烏龜</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>AQUATIC ANIMAL which HAS a HARD SHELL, AND IS FAMOUS for its LONG LIFE.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. Yuán tuó 黿鼉 refers generically to river reptiles.</p>
<p>2. The current general term for turtles is guī 龜, but the word tends to refer specifically to marine turtles.</p>
<p>3. Biē 鱉 refers to the ordinary soft-shelled turtle with a legendary biting power, a culinary delicacy.</p>
<p>4. Áo 鼇 refers to the giant sea turtle.</p>
<p>5. Yuán 黿 refers to a large variety of the soft-shelled sea turtle.</p>
        </div>
